                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.796/466: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-03T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 3, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>286. Your 387, October 2, 10 p.m. We are delighted that the contract has been
                    signed. We hope that the Ecuadoran Government will now proceed without delay in
                    the cancellation of Sedta’s franchise, thus completing the elimination of
                        Sedta.<note n="75" xml:id="d237fn75">An Evaluating Committee was appointed
                        to make a report to the Ecuadoran Minister of Defense concerning the
                        properties of Sedta; this was followed by liquidation.</note> Please press
                    this matter with the Ecuadoran officials.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
